722739f-a.title: Manhattan: Riverside Drive - 99th Street (West)
722739f-a.text:
(1)
999th To 100 Street West and Riverside Drive
shosing residence where Vaughan Kester wrote his first
novel,"Tho Manager of the BiA.",1901. Later on he
purchased Gunston Hall,Fairfax County,Virginia,(about
1900),the home of George Mason.
Ref.Tho's Who in America 1910-11
New York Times,JulE 6th,1911.
Vaughan Kester B.Sept.12,I869
D.July 4th,1211.
(2 ) The same.
(3) The same.
(4)  The same.
No Record of Photographer. (Information from Paul Kester
his brother.)
